# ‚ö° Quick Model Switching - 30 Second Guide

## Problem Solved ‚úÖ

**Before:** `/model glm/glm-4` (18 characters, wastes credits)
**Now:** `/glm` (4 characters, instant switch!)

## All Shortcuts

```
/glm              # GLM-4 (free, fast)
/glm-flash        # GLM-4-Flash (fastest)
/glm-air          # GLM-4-Air (balanced)

/featherless      # Llama-3-8B (uncensored)
/featherless-70b  # Llama-3-70B (larger)

/gemini           # Gemini Pro
/gemini-flash     # Gemini 2.0 Flash

/sonnet           # Back to Claude Sonnet 4.5
```

## How to Use

1. **Start clauded:**
   ```bash
   clauded
   ```

2. **Switch models instantly:**
   ```
   /glm
   ```

3. **See all shortcuts:**
   ```
   /models
   ```

That's it! üöÄ

## Why This Works

- **Custom commands** = Pre-written instructions (not user input)
- **No typing** = No wasted credits
- **Instant** = Switches immediately without confirmation
- **Safe** = No binary modification required

## Comparison

| Method | Characters | Credits Used | Speed |
|--------|-----------|--------------|-------|
| Manual typing | 18 chars | High | Slow |
| Custom shortcuts | 4 chars | Minimal | Instant ‚ö° |

## What About the `/model` Picker?

The built-in `/model` picker **can't** be modified (it's hardcoded in the binary). But these shortcuts are actually **better** because:

1. ‚úÖ Faster to type (4 chars vs 18)
2. ‚úÖ Uses fewer credits (pre-written instructions)
3. ‚úÖ No confirmation needed (instant switch)
4. ‚úÖ Easy to remember names
5. ‚úÖ Safe (no binary patching required)

## Advanced: Binary Patching

If you still want to modify the picker, check out:
- [tweakcc](https://github.com/Piebald-AI/tweakcc) - Patches Claude Code binary
- ‚ö†Ô∏è Requires reinstalling after updates
- ‚ö†Ô∏è Currently doesn't support model picker customization

**Recommendation:** Stick with shortcuts - they're better!

